By: Chang Po-tuan
---
When he has finished the banquet at Hua-ch’ih (Beautiful Pond) where the
moon shines brightly, he (the accomplished) rides on a golden dragon to
visit Tzû-wei (the star gods). From that time onward, when all of the hsien
(Immortals) have been interviewed, he rides above wide mountains and wherever
he likes.
